cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the application of classification methods for character recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of artificial neural networks (ANNs) and support vector machines (SVMs) also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of multiple classifiers and feature extraction techniques indicates the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
